
CreateLink(1)                  Scilab function                  CreateLink(1)
NAME
  CreateLink - creates a link between two applications

CALLING SEQUENCE
  CreateLink(appli1,appli2)

PARAMETERS

  appli1, name of an application
         : string

  appli2 : string, name of an application

DESCRIPTION
  CreateLink creates a link from appli1 to appli2.  Note that this link is
  directed.  This link being created, appli1 can send messages to appli2 and
  appli2 can receive messages from appli1.

  If the name of appli1 or appli2 is "SELF", it corresponds to the name of
  the application where we execute CreateLink.

  If the name of appli1 or appli2 is "XGeCI", it corresponds to the name of
  the first Scilab application started.

SEE ALSO
  DestroyLink, GetMsg, SendMsg
